Ever since childhood i had dreamed of working for the railroad.I met a woman while selling vacuums whose husband held a high position at our local train yard.This is my chance i thought so i had her to introduce me and i went and visited him daily for three weeks begging for a chance.He laughed me away each time.Finally one day he had had enough and yelled at me to be there firat thing early morning and not to ask any questions because i wouldnt be there long enough to need to wonder about hours or pay.I succeeded beyond belief and he was impressed and moved me up to a higher position.I was to be a track foreman. My first  job being a track foreman involved traveling to different places doing railroad work.My job was to do something called mud sealing. We were to use a scuba diver to go underwater with a hydraulic chainsaw  to cut the bridge pilons. So there was to be no train for the next 20 hours.The diver went under and cut 16 of the pilons.

   However nasa decided to take over the track and as heading back to Florida they had to cross our tracks which carried 16 scientists and 4 Booster Tanks.They called and asked and sd they had $240 billion worth of rocket boosters and very important scientists aboard and they were coming through.I urged them not to but after much insisting finally i replied "ok,just whatever you do Do Not Hit Your Brakes".

   Everything was going fine,we had moved all of our equiptment and cleared the path when a small gray haired bunny rabbit ran across,For whatever reason the engineer forgot everything we had discussed and hit his brakes.All at once the bridge started to sway and before you knew it the bridge had shifted sideways and the train along with the bridge fell to the ground. Scientists and all.Only about 4 were injured with minor cuts and bruises but the  bridge was unrecognizable.
